            "templateName": "imageAndTextBlock",
            "content": {
                "alignment": "left",
                "background": "#5f5b60",
                "img": {
                    "url": "assets/img/nodeMaterialEditor.png",
                    "alt": "Node material nodes wired together in a basic shader.",
                    "width": "550px"
                },
                "height": "400px",
                "marginLeft": "50px",
                "marginRight": "50px",
                "title": "Node Material Editor",
                "desc": "Introducing the powerful and simple Node Material Editor. This new user-friendly node based system unlocks the power of the GPU for everyone. Traditionally, writing shaders (GPU programs) hasn't been very easy or accessible for anyone without the understanding of low level code. Babylon's new node material system removes the complexity without sacrificing power. With this new system, absolutely anyone can create beautiful shader networks by simply connecting nodes together.",
                "moreInfoLink": "https://doc.babylonjs.com/how_to/node_material",
                "moreInfoText": "More on Node Materials"
            }
        },
        {
            "templateName": "imageAndTextBlock",
            "content": {
                "alignment": "right",
                "background": "#2a2342",
                "img": {
                    "url": "assets/img/babylonNative_identity_dark.png",
                    "alt": "Babylon Native logo",
                    "width": "550px"
                },
                "height": "400px",
                "marginLeft": "50px",
                "marginRight": "50px",
                "title": "Babylon Native Preview",
                "desc": "The holy grail of software development is to write code once and have it work absolutely everywhere: on any device, on every platform. This is the inspiration behind Babylon Native. This exciting new addition to the Babylon platform allows anyone to take their Babylon.js code and build a native application with it, unlocking the power of native technologies.",
                "moreInfoLink": "/native",
                "moreInfoText": "More on Babylon Native"
            }
        },   
        {
            "templateName": "imageAndTextBlock",
            "content": {
                "alignment": "left",
                "background": "#29333b",
                "img": {
                    "url": "assets/img/agents.png",
                    "alt": "3D fish models swimming in a school using AI navigation mesh.",
                    "width": "550px"
                },
                "height": "400px",
                "marginLeft": "50px",
                "marginRight": "50px",
                "title": "Navigation Mesh and Crowd Agents",
                "desc": "With the new fun and simple Navigation Mesh system, leveraging the power of the excellent and open-source Recast navigation library, it's easier than ever to create convincing \"AI\" for your game or interactive experience. Simply provide a crowd agent with a navigation mesh, and the movement of that agent will be confined to the mesh. As seen with the fish in this Underwater Demo, you'll find it very useful for AI and path finding or to replace physics for collision detection (only allow player to go where it's possible instead of using collision detection).",
                "moreInfoLink": "https://doc.babylonjs.com/extensions/navigationmesh",
                "moreInfoText": "More on Navigation Mesh and Crowd Agents"
            }
        }, 
        {      
            "templateName": "imageAndTextBlock",
            "content": {
                "alignment": "right",
                "background": "#163035",
                "img": {
                    "url": "assets/img/vr.png",
                    "alt": "Photo of a Microsoft VR motion controller.",
                    "width": "550px"
                },
                "height": "400px",
                "marginLeft": "50px",
                "marginRight": "50px",
                "title": "Updated WebXR Support",
                "desc": "It's no secret that the future is bright for AR/VR experiences on the web. Babylon 4.1 further advances the engine's best-in-class WebXR support by bringing an easy to use experience helper, a dedicated session manager for more advanced users, one camera to rule them all, full support for any device that accepts WebXR sessions, full input-source support, API for Experimental AR features, teleportation, scene interactions, physics, and more.",
                "moreInfoLink": "https://doc.babylonjs.com/how_to/introduction_to_webxr",
                "moreInfoText": "More on WebXR"
            }
        },       
